			<ns0:name>robe...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108771824208521698652/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">I disagree with Mark on this one. It is the job of the OS (service runtime in this case) to start a program in a state that is compatible with the ABI
for the platform. For ARM this means 8byte alignment of the stack
Fixing this in the startup code as we do now is a pretty ugly kludge and does not work with the barebones tests which do not use any startup code.


